             sworn.</p>
               <p>I apprehended the prisoner; I found nothing on him.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>My wife nursed Mrs. Knight's two children; I called on her for some shillings, part of what she owed me; and I saw her so bad that I said nothing of the money; I treated her with a glass of peppermint, and told Mr. Smith, to let her know where I was, if she wanted me.</p>
               <p>Court to Jury. There being a mistake in the indictment; calling him 
               <persName id="t17890909-147-person1270">
                  John
                   Kent
               <interp inst="t17890909-147-person1270" type="surname" value="Kent"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890909-147-person1270" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890909-147-person1270" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             instead of Henry, takes off the capital part of the charge.</p>
